<emphasis id="F003B15DB8C85FE3585D5B534AF7F949" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">T. spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="CECE4473F044969E24398DCA6DAE1C00" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">31</emphasis>
male antennomeres IV and V of 
<taxonomicName id="C1CBAAD73A68AE76D8D2FB65CC9CE6CC" class="Insecta" genus="T." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="T. callosa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="callosa">
<emphasis id="9CE2D62820A20E36DE83F16DE0BEFB0D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">T. callosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Abbreviations: 
<emphasis id="9356CA13C1884848607FC86476969405" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P</emphasis>
pit-like sensillum 
<emphasis id="D93DEFBFB8F08FB392906B48AAF51375" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">SB</emphasis>
an area of sensilla basiconica.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="3690F0573B0AB4159B5F01D878DBF909" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Pronotum slightly longer than wide, widest at middle, with fine dense punctures. Mesoventrite with short anterior process.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A941DF842C24A418CE0EF2E12969888" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Elytra oblong, parallel sided, covered with ten striae; striae I-III absent before basal oblique yellow fascia; IV-VI extending after middle; VII and VIII weakly punctured after base of lateral yellow fascia; IX and X obscuse.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6BBDF32C53512C7C2399E3C130BB2714" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tibiae stout, with longitudinal carina; tibial spur formula 1-2-2; tarsal pulvillar formula 4-4-4; pro- and mesotarsomeres I and II with large lobed pulvilli; III and IV with large bilobed pulvilli; metatarsomeres I with vestigial minute pulvillus; II with small lobed pulvillus; III and IV with large bilobed pulvilli; claws with basal denticles.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA8D301BCF48FEEE847EFDA9A15C0638" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Abdominal sternite V deeply, marginated at apical margin. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5B7E084E77F1D99AED20B6AF93E787AC" captionStart="Figures 41–50" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 41 - 50. Male terminal parts and aedeagus 41 - 45 Tillicera fortis sp. nov. 46 - 50 T. spinosa sp. nov. 41, 46 pygidium 42, 47 ventrite VI 43, 48 spicular fork 44, 49 tegmen in lateral (a), ventral (b) and dorsal (c) views 45, 50 median lobe in lateral (a), ventral (b), and dorsal (c) views." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures41-50" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672271" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">41</figureCitation>
) almost transverse at apical margin; ventrite VI (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="691D4ACF82D4862395530DA9DABDD4F0" captionStart="Figures 41–50" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 41 - 50. Male terminal parts and aedeagus 41 - 45 Tillicera fortis sp. nov. 46 - 50 T. spinosa sp. nov. 41, 46 pygidium 42, 47 ventrite VI 43, 48 spicular fork 44, 49 tegmen in lateral (a), ventral (b) and dorsal (c) views 45, 50 median lobe in lateral (a), ventral (b), and dorsal (c) views." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures41-50" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672271" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">42</figureCitation>
) broadly emarginated at apical margin; spicular fork (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8D7C0FCADB82631C03AFCDD4C79A3CEE" captionStart="Figures 41–50" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 41 - 50. Male terminal parts and aedeagus 41 - 45 Tillicera fortis sp. nov. 46 - 50 T. spinosa sp. nov. 41, 46 pygidium 42, 47 ventrite VI 43, 48 spicular fork 44, 49 tegmen in lateral (a), ventral (b) and dorsal (c) views 45, 50 median lobe in lateral (a), ventral (b), and dorsal (c) views." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures41-50" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672271" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">43</figureCitation>
) long, without intraspicular plate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1884000417E0C9C62089B42FFC53693E" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Tegmen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D6F2BBC15D9CC66C65537805858DE3CE" captionStart="Figures 41–50" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 41 - 50. Male terminal parts and aedeagus 41 - 45 Tillicera fortis sp. nov. 46 - 50 T. spinosa sp. nov. 41, 46 pygidium 42, 47 ventrite VI 43, 48 spicular fork 44, 49 tegmen in lateral (a), ventral (b) and dorsal (c) views 45, 50 median lobe in lateral (a), ventral (b), and dorsal (c) views." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures41-50" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672271" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">44a-c</figureCitation>
) with dorsal and ventral sinus at apical 1/4; parameroid lobes tapered posteriorly at apex in lateral view, flattened at apex; tegminal arms short, extending middle to basal 1/4 of total length. Median lobe (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="03FA3FFBF78A0EC1A06D6932D96DE500" captionStart="Figures 41–50" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figures 41 - 50. Male terminal parts and aedeagus 41 - 45 Tillicera fortis sp. nov. 46 - 50 T. spinosa sp. nov. 41, 46 pygidium 42, 47 ventrite VI 43, 48 spicular fork 44, 49 tegmen in lateral (a), ventral (b) and dorsal (c) views 45, 50 median lobe in lateral (a), ventral (b), and dorsal (c) views." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures41-50" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672271" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">45a-c</figureCitation>
) slightly shorter than tegmen; plates with rows of denticles on apex of dorsal and ventral sides, on left side in ventral view these are positioned at apical 1/5, on right side in ventral view they are very short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2DCC69F8A20E64E4E7E76BC8E069997E" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="AB8DE2A5A5D1010C7FB9961E02AAEE53" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male but distinguished by the following characteristics: antennomere XI without pit-like sensillum; sternite V with shallower emargination at apical margin. Elytral striae VI to VIII weakly punctured posterior to base of lateral yellow fascia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
