<subSubSection id="8C1AB4B18FDE1C24D964DFC3E16FE3BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="9E8D4DB89868E68A0B55B6C95DCF7351" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="60D22C7AC59DB32550DF6B0A81AE8D05" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This specific name is derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName id="9258AA379AA3350E20566329C8491EEE" authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Murakami &amp; Gerstmeier &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera fortis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortis">
<emphasis id="058E4126DC74923E0A469AB418BDEF1D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera fortis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sturdy), referring to the stout tibiae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
